Rand Erases Its Drop, South African Stocks Pare Retreat on U.S. Jobs Data

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-08-05T12:38:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/rand-erases-its-drop-south-african-stocks-pare-retreat-on-u-s-jobs-data.html
The rand rebounded from a two-week
low and South African stocks pared their decline after U.S.
employers added more jobs than forecast in July, easing concern
the worldâ€™s biggest economy is grinding to a halt.  The rand appreciated as much as 0.5 percent and traded 0.2
percent stronger at 6.9083 by 2:34 p.m. in Johannesburg after
earlier retreating as much as 0.6 percent to the weakest since
July 19. The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index traded 1 percent
down at 29,312.99, paring a loss of as much as 3.3 percent.  Payrolls rose by 117,000 workers after a 46,000 increase in
June that was more than originally estimated, Labor Department
data showed today in  Washington . The median estimate in a
Bloomberg News survey called for a July gain of 85,000. The
jobless rate dropped to 9.1 percent as more Americans left the
 labor force , while average hourly earnings climbed 0.4 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
